%N A394556 a(n) is the smallest m not divisible by (n-1)! such that sigma(m) = n*m/2.
%C A394556 Position of a(n) among numbers with abundancy n/2 for n = 4..13: 2, 2, 2, 2, 2, 2, 3, 7, 37, 24.
%C A394556 An upper bound of a(14), 236008579722503605737831375688048524282888116491737299671140729618369065641395335345555374080, is given by _Michel Marcus_, Mar 24 2026. It has a position of at least 73 among numbers with abundancy 7 (see the link of Achim Flammenkamp).
